<subSubSection id="68AA6541B85CFFAFFF62024BCC53F9D9" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="200F36CAB85CFFAFFF62024BC86EFAE1" blockId="5.[151,1436,1288,1623]" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">
This small section was not recognized as a distinct entity in any of the main twentieth-century classifications (
<bibRefCitation id="44214B3BB85CFFAFFF6B026DCC1FFAC6" author="Pascher, A." box="[158,322,1326,1352]" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" pagination="109 - 131" refId="ref10037" refString="Pascher, A. (1904) Ubersicht uber die Arten der Gattung Gagea. Sitzungberichte des Deutschen naturwissenschaflichmedicischen Vereins fur Bohmen ' Lotos' 24: 109 - 131." type="journal article" year="1904">Pascher 1904</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="44214B3BB85CFFAFFEBA026DCCD0FAC6" author="Pascher, A." box="[335,397,1326,1352]" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" pagination="353 - 375" refId="ref10067" refString="Pascher, A. (1907) Conspectus Gagearum Asiae. Bulletin de la Societe Imperiale des Naturalistes de Moscou 19: 353 - 375." type="journal article" year="1907">1907</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="44214B3BB85CFFAFFE6F026DCF7DFAC6" author="Stroh, G." box="[410,544,1326,1352]" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" pagination="485 - 520" refId="ref10868" refString="Stroh, G. (1937) Die Gattung Gagea Salisb. Beihefte zum Botanischen Centralblatt 57: 485 - 520." type="journal article" year="1937">Stroh 1937</bibRefCitation>
). All species of this section were placed in 
<emphasis id="12C4EAD8B85CFFAFFBD3026CC962FAC6" box="[1062,1087,1327,1352]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName id="E7B04D49B85CFFAFFB71026CC873FAC6" authority="G.F.Hoffmann, 1814" authorityName="G.F.Hoffmann" authorityYear="1814" box="[1156,1326,1327,1352]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Platyspermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="12C4EAD8B85CFFAFFB71026CC873FAC6" box="[1156,1326,1327,1352]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">Platyspermum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="44214B3BB85CFFAFFAA9026DCDB5FAE1" author="Stroh, G." pageId="5" pageNumber="49" pagination="485 - 520" refId="ref10868" refString="Stroh, G. (1937) Die Gattung Gagea Salisb. Beihefte zum Botanischen Centralblatt 57: 485 - 520." type="journal article" year="1937">Stroh (1937)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="44214B3BB85CFFAFFF010216CCC0FAE1" author="Pascher, A." box="[244,413,1365,1391]" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" pagination="109 - 131" refId="ref10037" refString="Pascher, A. (1904) Ubersicht uber die Arten der Gattung Gagea. Sitzungberichte des Deutschen naturwissenschaflichmedicischen Vereins fur Bohmen ' Lotos' 24: 109 - 131." type="journal article" year="1904">Pascher (1904</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="44214B3BB85CFFAFFE5C0216CCB8FAE1" author="Pascher, A." box="[425,485,1365,1391]" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" pagination="353 - 375" refId="ref10067" refString="Pascher, A. (1907) Conspectus Gagearum Asiae. Bulletin de la Societe Imperiale des Naturalistes de Moscou 19: 353 - 375." type="journal article" year="1907">1907</bibRefCitation>
) placed 
<taxonomicName id="E7B04D49B85CFFAFFDBD0216C95EFAE1" authority="(Viv.) Greuter (1970: 159)" authorityName="Greuter" authorityPageNumber="159" authorityYear="1970" baseAuthorityName="Viv." box="[584,1027,1365,1391]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trinerva">
<emphasis id="12C4EAD8B85CFFAFFDBD0216CF9AFAE0" box="[584,711,1365,1390]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">G. trinerva</emphasis>
(Viv.) 
<bibRefCitation id="44214B3BB85CFFAFFCED0216C95EFAE1" author="Greuter, W." box="[792,1027,1365,1391]" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" pagination="155 - 160" refId="ref9146" refString="Greuter, W. (1970) The taxonomic position of Lloydia graeca (Liliaceae) and related species. Israel Journal of Botany 19: 155 - 160." type="journal article" year="1970">Greuter (1970: 159)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E7B04D49B85CFFAFFBC90216C9ECFAE0" box="[1084,1201,1365,1390]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="graeca">
<emphasis id="12C4EAD8B85CFFAFFBC90216C9ECFAE0" box="[1084,1201,1365,1390]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">G. graeca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName id="E7B04D49B85CFFAFFB260216C871FAE0" authorityName=", Xinqi &amp; Turland" authorityYear="2000" box="[1235,1324,1365,1390]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Phallaceae" genus="Lloydia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Phallales" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="12C4EAD8B85CFFAFFB260216C871FAE0" box="[1235,1324,1365,1390]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">Lloydia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="200F36CAB85CFFAFFF62023FCC53F9D9" blockId="5.[151,1436,1288,1623]" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">
<bibRefCitation id="44214B3BB85CFFAFFF62023FCCF7FA18" author="Peruzzi, L. &amp; Tison, J. - M. &amp; Peterson, A. &amp; Peterson, J." box="[151,426,1404,1430]" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" pagination="1201 - 1214" refId="ref10194" refString="Peruzzi, L., Tison, J. - M., Peterson, A. &amp; Peterson, J. (2008 b) On the phylogenetic position and taxonomic value of Gagea trinervia (Viv.) Greuter and the whole G. sect. Anthericoides A. Terracc. (Liliaceae). Taxon 57: 1201 - 1214." type="journal article" year="2008">
Peruzzi 
<emphasis id="12C4EAD8B85CFFAFFF0B023FCC63FA1B" box="[254,318,1404,1429]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">et al.</emphasis>
(2008b)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="44214B3BB85CFFAFFE1F023FCFA1FA18" author="Peterson, A. &amp; Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J." box="[490,764,1404,1430]" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" pagination="446 - 465" refId="ref10393" refString="Peterson, A., Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J. (2008) Systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae) and infrageneric classification of Gagea based on molecular and morphological data. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 46: 446 - 465." type="journal article" year="2008">
Peterson 
<emphasis id="12C4EAD8B85CFFAFFDAA023FCFC2FA1B" box="[607,671,1404,1429]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
accepted this section as distinct. The former authors mentioned only two species (
<taxonomicName id="E7B04D49B85CFFAFFDF702E0CFDBFA32" authorityName="Greuter" authorityYear="1970" baseAuthorityName="Viv." box="[514,646,1443,1468]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trinerva">
<emphasis id="12C4EAD8B85CFFAFFDF702E0CFDBFA32" box="[514,646,1443,1468]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">G. trinerva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E7B04D49B85CFFAFFD3002E0CE61FA32" box="[709,828,1443,1468]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="graeca">
<emphasis id="12C4EAD8B85CFFAFFD3002E0CE61FA32" box="[709,828,1443,1468]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">G. graeca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) in this section, but in the latter there were three species. 
<taxonomicName id="E7B04D49B85CFFAFFF0E028ACF6CFA6C" box="[251,561,1481,1507]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Anthericoides">
<emphasis id="12C4EAD8B85CFFAFFF0E028ACC14FA6C" box="[251,329,1481,1506]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">Gagea</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis id="12C4EAD8B85CFFAFFE7B028ACF6CFA6C" box="[398,561,1481,1506]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">Anthericoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is sister to the rest of the genus in the analyses performed by 
<bibRefCitation id="44214B3BB85CFFAFFAE4028ACDB9F984" author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Wilkin, P. &amp; Fay, M. F. &amp; Ingrouille, M. J. &amp; Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W." pageId="5" pageNumber="49" pagination="125 - 142" refId="ref11349" refString="Zarrei, M., Wilkin, P., Fay, M. F., Ingrouille, M. J., Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2009) Molecular systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae; Liliales): implications of analyses of nuclear ribosomal and plastid sequences for infrageneric classification. Annals of Botany 104: 125 - 142." type="journal article" year="2009">
Zarrei 
<emphasis id="12C4EAD8B85CFFAFFA95028AC8C1FA6C" box="[1376,1436,1481,1506]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="49">et al.</emphasis>
(2009)
</bibRefCitation>
and includes members that are endemic to the Mediterranean region. The possession of white flowers with tepals longer than 
<quantity id="E7489B2FB85CFFAFFE5E0155CCA0F9BE" box="[427,509,1558,1584]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="49" unit="mm" value="12.0">12 mm</quantity>
is a shared morphological characteristic of this section, which we recognise in this study.
</paragraph>
